# BetLab Frontend

- Frontend app name is `BetLab`.
- Build frontend with Vite + React + JavaScript (`.jsx` / `.js`), not TypeScript.
- Keep tools modular and independent in `frontend/src/tools`.
- Route each tool from `frontend/src/App.jsx` so tools can be added without touching shared logic heavily.
- Maintain process/style docs in `docs/frontend-process.md`.

# Core UI Structure

- Global layout component: `frontend/src/components/AppLayout.jsx`.
- App navigation uses a top-header system with primary links and grouped dropdown menus, with a mobile menu pattern at smaller widths.
- Shared app state (favorites, history, notes): `frontend/src/state/BetLabContext.jsx`.
- Tool metadata source of truth: `frontend/src/data/tools.js`.
- Reusable utilities (odds conversion, storage, formatters) belong in `frontend/src/utils`.
- Reusable hooks belong in `frontend/src/hooks`.
- Theme state is stored in `betlab.theme` and applied via `data-theme` on document root.
- For numeric tool inputs, default to `type="number"` with incremental stepping (`step="1"` unless tool-specific precision needs differ).
- Numeric incrementers must be visually validated in dark/light mode and styled via scoped classes in `frontend/src/styles.css`.

# MVP Tool Set

- Odds Converter (`/tools/odds-converter`)
- Bet Size Calculator (`/tools/bet-size`)
- Parlay Builder (`/tools/parlay`)
- Quick Notes (`/tools/quick-notes`)
- Overlay Calculator (`/tools/overlay-calculator`)
- Round Leader Projection (`/tools/round-leader-projection`)
- Probability Calculator (`/tools/probability-calculator`)
- Basketball Modeling (`/tools/basketball-modeling`)

# Local Persistence

- Use localStorage for early-stage persistence:
  - `betlab.favorites`
  - `betlab.history`
  - `betlab.notes`
  - `betlab.theme`
- Keep history capped to latest 25 entries.
- Ensure UI remains readable and functional in both dark and light themes.

# Round Leader Projection UX

- Keep manual tournament URL input available as a fallback.
- Prefer loading event-picker options from backend cached schedule data.
- Include a subtle refresh affordance so users can explicitly update schedule events on demand.
- Selecting an event in the event picker should only set/highlight the URL target; do not auto-scrape until the user presses `Scrape and Project`.
- Show a stat-selection panel below the tournament URL input with defaults: `Course (Hole) Model`, `Par 3 Scoring Avg`, `Par 4 Scoring Avg`, `Par 5 Scoring Avg`.
- Include a `Blended Model` checkbox at the bottom of the stat-selection panel; when enabled, send `projectionModel: "blended"` so backend blends Par and SG skill adjustments instead of stacking them fully.
- Include an optional weather controls panel for Round projections (`AM wave adjustment`, `PM wave adjustment`, `wind volatility multiplier`) and send these as `weatherOverrides`.
- Provide an optional SG CSV file input below the stat-selection panel; when no file is uploaded, fall back to the latest backend SG CSV.
- Validate uploaded SG CSV structure at upload time and show clear inline status feedback (`validating`, `OK`, detected schema, or error) near the file input.
- Enforce SG exclusivity in UI: if `SG: Total` is selected, SG component stats must be unselected/disabled, and vice versa.
- Enforce `SG: Tee-to-Green` overlap rules in UI: it cannot be selected with `SG: Off-the-Tee`, `SG: Approach`, or `SG: Around-the-Green`, but it can be selected with `SG: Putting`.
- Keep stat-specific upload inputs directly below their related checkbox groups: SG upload below Strokes Gained and Recent Form upload below Recent Form.
- Enable the SG upload only when at least one SG metric is selected, and enable the Recent Form upload only when `Recent Form L20` is selected.
- Show a simple `Recent Form L20` weight input next to its checkbox/label, defaulting to `0.30`, and send it as `recentFormWeight`.
- Recent Form uploads should validate DataGolf group trending CSVs and send `uploadedRecentFormCsv` with projection requests only when `Recent Form L20` is selected.
- Brand the module as `Golf Projection`.
- Player projections should support tabbing between `Round Leader`, `Tournament`, and `Group Winner` projection scopes.
- The `Group Winner` tab should let users select 2-4 tournament players, display only those selected players, show raw group `Win Tie %`, and show dead-heat adjusted group placement probabilities instead of tournament top-finish columns.
- Player projections table should include sortable `Win/Tie Pct` and `FV` columns between `Remaining` and `Projected`.
- On the `Round Leader` tab, include sortable `Top 10` and `Top 5` columns using dead-heat adjusted top-finish fair values for the current round.
- On the `Tournament` tab, include sortable `Top 20`, `Top 10`, and `Top 5` columns using dead-heat adjusted top-finish fair values (cents), and keep trailing column order as `Top 20`, `Top 10`, `Top 5`, `Win`, `Projected`.
- In Player Projections, keep score columns showing score values; for players awaiting a round start with a tee time, display the tee time in the `Thru` column instead of replacing the score display.
- `Thru` sorting should use tee times for players awaiting round start, and completed-hole progress for players already in-round.
- Show a warning icon next to player names when any selected projection stat is missing and using a fallback value; tooltip text should list the missing Par/SG stat labels.
- Show a compact manual-override icon next to player names when any stat or score input source is `manual_override` and differs from its `baselineValue`; tooltip text should list only the meaningfully overridden fields.
- Show an edit icon next to each player in projections that opens a modal for stat overrides on currently selected per-player stats.
- The edit modal should also support manual score overrides (`Total Score`, `Round Score`, `Completed Holes`) for faster live correction.
- Applying modal edits should trigger a projection refresh and preserve table scope/tab context.
- Keep an `Export CSV` button beside the projections refresh control and export every player row in the active projection scope with grid values plus all per-player stat input columns.

# Growth Direction

- Add future tools as isolated modules in `src/tools`.
- Keep frontend API calls behind a dedicated client layer before wiring Express/Mongo persistence.
